<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical} og={og} schema={schema} active={active}>
<!-- ═══ PAGE HEADER ═══ -->
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Bed Bug Treatment in Southern Utah</h1>
    <p>Discreet inspections, heat and targeted treatments, and guaranteed elimination from St. George's trusted local pest control team.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ AI SUMMARY BLOCK (Layer 1) ═══ -->
  <section class="section" style="padding-bottom:0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="reveal" style="max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; background: var(--gray-light, #f5f5f5); border-radius: 12px; padding: 24px 28px;">
        <p style="margin:0; color: var(--dark, #1a1a1a); line-height: 1.7;"><strong>Wernex Termite &amp; Pest Control</strong> provides professional bed bug treatment for homes, apartments, hotels, and vacation rentals across St. George, Washington, Hurricane, Ivins, Santa Clara, and all of Washington County — part of our <a href="pest-control-southern-utah.html">complete Southern Utah service area</a>. Services include free discreet inspections, whole-room heat treatments that kill bed bugs and eggs in a single visit, targeted residual treatments, and follow-up monitoring to confirm elimination. Licensed, insured, and family-owned since 1994. <a href="tel:+14356739503">Call (435) 673-9503</a> for fast, confidential scheduling.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ WHY SOUTHERN UTAH ═══ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="reveal">
          <span class="section-label">The Local Picture</span>
          <h2>Why Bed Bugs Are a Growing Problem in Southern Utah</h2>
          <p style="margin: 16px 0; color: var(--gray);">Bed bugs are not a sign of a dirty home — they are expert hitchhikers that travel from place to place in luggage, backpacks, purses, and secondhand furniture. They feed on human blood at night and spend the day hidden in mattress seams, box springs, headboards, and the tiny cracks around baseboards and outlets. A single fertilized female can start a new infestation, and populations grow quickly once they are established.</p>
          <p style="color: var(--gray);">Southern Utah is unusually exposed to bed bug introductions because of how much the region depends on travel. St. George sits at the gateway to <a href="pest-control-near-zion-national-park.html">Zion National Park</a>, Snow Canyon State Park, and Tuacahn, and Washington County draws millions of visitors a year for its national parks, golf resorts, and warm-weather events. That constant flow of overnight guests moves through hotels, resorts, and the area's thousands of short-term <a href="pest-control-vacation-rentals-southern-utah.html">vacation rentals and Airbnbs</a> — every one of which is a potential point of contact.</p>
          <p style="color: var(--gray);">Our large population of snowbirds and retirees adds another layer of risk. Seasonal residents travel back and forth between Utah and other states, and visiting family members bring luggage from all over the country. Utah Tech University in St. George brings in students and their belongings each semester, and senior-living and multi-family housing can let an infestation spread between units. None of this means you did anything wrong — it simply means bed bugs are easy to encounter and worth taking seriously the moment you suspect them.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reveal">
          <img src="images/42.webp" alt="Bed bug on a hotel mattress in Southern Utah — how to check your room for bed bugs" style="width:100%; height:100%; min-height:340px; object-fit:cover; border-radius:16px; box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,.18);" loading="lazy">
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ TREATMENT OPTIONS ═══ -->
  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-center reveal">
        <span class="section-label">How We Treat</span>
        <h2>Bed Bug Treatment Options for Southern Utah Homes &amp; Rentals</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="service-cards" style="margin-top: 40px;">
        <a href="contact.html" class="service-card reveal">
          <div class="service-card__icon service-card__icon--amber">🔍</div>
          <h3>Free Inspection &amp; ID</h3>
          <p>We confirm whether you actually have bed bugs — many bites are blamed on bed bugs but caused by fleas, mites, or other pests. We map every room and harborage point so nothing is missed, and provide a clear, no-obligation quote.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="contact.html" class="service-card reveal">
          <div class="service-card__icon service-card__icon--green">🔥</div>
          <h3>Heat Treatment</h3>
          <p>We raise the room to a temperature that is lethal to bed bugs and their eggs in a single visit. Heat penetrates mattresses, furniture, and wall voids that sprays can't reach — and it leaves no chemical residue behind.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="contact.html" class="service-card reveal">
          <div class="service-card__icon service-card__icon--green">🎯</div>
          <h3>Targeted Treatment</h3>
          <p>Professional-grade residual products applied precisely to seams, frames, baseboards, and cracks where bed bugs travel and hide. Often combined with heat for stubborn or widespread infestations.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="contact.html" class="service-card reveal">
          <div class="service-card__icon service-card__icon--amber">📋</div>
          <h3>Follow-Up &amp; Monitoring</h3>
          <p>Bed bug eggs can hatch after the first treatment, so we schedule follow-up visits and monitoring to confirm the infestation is fully gone — not just knocked down. Peace of mind backed by our guarantee.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ WARNING SIGNS ═══ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="reveal">
          <img src="images/26.webp" alt="Wernex technician inspecting a Southern Utah property for bed bugs with a flashlight" style="width:100%; height:100%; min-height:300px; object-fit:cover; border-radius:16px; box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,.18);" loading="lazy">
        </div>
        <div class="reveal">
          <span class="section-label">Warning Signs</span>
          <h2>How to Tell If You Have Bed Bugs</h2>
          <p style="margin: 16px 0; color: var(--gray);">Bed bugs are small — about the size and color of an apple seed when fully grown — and they are very good at staying hidden. Most people discover an infestation from the evidence it leaves behind rather than by seeing the bugs themselves. Here is what our technicians look for, and what you can check between visits:</p>
          <p style="color: var(--gray);"><strong>Bites in lines or clusters</strong> are often the first clue. Bed bug bites typically appear on skin exposed during sleep — arms, shoulders, legs, and neck — and frequently show up in a row or tight group. Not everyone reacts to the bites, so their absence doesn't rule out an infestation.</p>
          <p style="color: var(--gray);"><strong>Spots and stains</strong> on bedding are a reliable sign. Look for tiny rust-colored or dark spots (digested blood) along mattress seams, on sheets, and where the mattress meets the box spring, plus small smears on the headboard and nearby walls.</p>
          <p style="color: var(--gray);"><strong>Shed skins and eggs</strong> accumulate where bed bugs harbor. As they grow, bed bugs molt and leave behind pale, translucent shells; the eggs are about a millimeter long and cream-colored, often tucked into cracks and seams.</p>
          <p style="color: var(--gray);"><strong>A musty, sweet odor</strong> can develop in rooms with a heavy infestation. If you notice any of these signs, avoid moving belongings between rooms — that can spread the problem — and <a href="contact.html">contact us</a> for a discreet inspection right away.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ PROCESS ═══ -->
  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-center reveal">
        <span class="section-label">Our Process</span>
        <h2>What to Expect From a Wernex Bed Bug Treatment</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="cards-grid" style="margin-top: 40px; max-width: 960px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
        <div class="card reveal">
          <div class="card__body">
            <h3>1. Discreet Inspection</h3>
            <p style="color:var(--gray);">A licensed Wernex technician arrives in an unmarked-friendly, professional manner and inspects bedrooms, furniture, and adjacent rooms to confirm the infestation, gauge its severity, and identify every harborage point. You receive a clear treatment recommendation and a no-obligation quote.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card reveal">
          <div class="card__body">
            <h3>2. Preparation &amp; Treatment</h3>
            <p style="color:var(--gray);">We give you a simple prep checklist beforehand so treatment day goes smoothly. Depending on the plan, we apply whole-room heat, targeted residual products, or both — reaching mattresses, frames, baseboards, and wall voids where bed bugs hide.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card reveal">
          <div class="card__body">
            <h3>3. Follow-Up &amp; Guarantee</h3>
            <p style="color:var(--gray);">Because eggs can hatch after the initial service, we schedule follow-up visits and monitoring to verify the infestation is fully eliminated. Our work is backed by a satisfaction guarantee — if bed bugs persist within the covered period, we return.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ PREVENTION / TRAVEL ═══ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-center reveal">
        <span class="section-label">Prevention</span>
        <h2>How to Avoid Bringing Bed Bugs Home</h2>
        <p class="mx-auto" style="margin-top:12px;color:var(--gray);max-width:720px;">Because bed bugs travel with people, a few simple habits go a long way — especially in a region where so many of us travel for work, visit family out of state, or host guests during park season.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cards-grid" style="margin-top: 40px; max-width: 1000px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
        <div class="card reveal">
          <div class="card__body">
            <h3>Inspect Where You Sleep</h3>
            <p style="color:var(--gray);">In hotels and vacation rentals, pull back the sheets and check the mattress seams, the corners of the box spring, and behind the headboard for rust-colored spots or live bugs before you settle in. It takes two minutes and is the single most effective habit.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card reveal">
          <div class="card__body">
            <h3>Keep Luggage Off the Floor</h3>
            <p style="color:var(--gray);">Use the luggage rack — pulled away from the wall — or keep bags in the bathtub while you inspect the room. Bed bugs travel from bedding and upholstered furniture into open suitcases, so the less contact, the better.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card reveal">
          <div class="card__body">
            <h3>Treat Bags After Travel</h3>
            <p style="color:var(--gray);">When you get home, unpack in the garage rather than the bedroom and run clothing through a hot dryer for 30 minutes — heat kills any hitchhikers. Wipe down hard-sided luggage and store it away from sleeping areas.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card reveal">
          <div class="card__body">
            <h3>Be Careful With Used Furniture</h3>
            <p style="color:var(--gray);">Secondhand mattresses, couches, and bed frames are a leading way bed bugs enter a home. Inspect any used furniture closely before bringing it inside — and never pick up discarded mattresses left at the curb.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-center reveal" style="margin-top:28px;color:var(--gray);max-width:760px;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;">If you manage a hotel, resort, or short-term rental in Washington County, proactive monitoring protects both your guests and your reviews. We work discreetly around booking schedules to keep units in service — see our <a href="pest-control-vacation-rentals-southern-utah.html">vacation rental pest control</a> options or <a href="contact.html">reach out</a> to set up a plan.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

