        <h2>Bed Bug Treatment FAQs — Southern Utah</h2>
      </div>
      <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 36px auto 0;">

        <div class="faq-item reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-light); padding: 24px 0;">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom: 8px;">How do I know if I have bed bugs in my Southern Utah home?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--gray);">The most common first sign is waking up with small, itchy bites in a line or cluster, usually on arms, legs, or the neck. Other signs include tiny rust-colored or black spots on sheets and mattress seams, pale yellow shed skins, and a faint sweet or musty odor in heavily infested rooms. Because bed bugs hide in mattress seams, box springs, headboards, and baseboard cracks, a professional inspection is the only reliable way to confirm an infestation.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-light); padding: 24px 0;">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Do bed bugs come from staying in hotels or vacation rentals?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--gray);">Yes. Bed bugs do not come from poor housekeeping — they are hitchhikers that travel in luggage, clothing, and used furniture. St. George and Southern Utah see heavy year-round tourism from <a href="pest-control-near-zion-national-park.html">Zion National Park</a>, Snow Canyon, Tuacahn, and the region's many golf resorts, and the area has thousands of short-term <a href="pest-control-vacation-rentals-southern-utah.html">vacation rentals</a>. That constant flow of overnight guests makes bed bug introductions more common here than many homeowners expect.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-light); padding: 24px 0;">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Does Wernex use heat treatment or chemicals for bed bugs?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--gray);">We use whichever approach fits the situation, and often a combination. Heat treatment raises the room temperature to a level lethal to bed bugs and their eggs in a single visit, reaching cracks and voids that sprays cannot. Targeted residual treatments place professional-grade products precisely where bed bugs harbor and travel. After assessing the level of infestation, your Wernex technician recommends the most effective and least disruptive plan for your home or rental.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-light); padding: 24px 0;">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom: 8px;">How much does bed bug treatment cost in St. George?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--gray);">Cost depends on the size of the property, the number of rooms affected, and how established the infestation is. Wernex provides a free, discreet bed bug inspection so you get an accurate, no-obligation quote before any work begins. <a href="contact.html">Contact us</a> or call <a href="tel:+14356739503">(435) 673-9503</a> to schedule.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item reveal" style="padding: 24px 0;">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Can I get rid of bed bugs myself with store-bought sprays?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--gray);">Rarely. Over-the-counter foggers and sprays kill a few visible bugs on contact but miss the eggs and the bugs hidden deep in seams, frames, and wall voids — and they can scatter the infestation into adjacent rooms. Many bed bug populations are also resistant to common consumer pesticides. Professional treatment that reaches every harborage point is the most reliable way to fully eliminate an infestation.</p>
        </div>

